<item>
            <title>[LANG-828] FastDateParser does not handle non-Gregorian calendars properly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LANG-828</link>
                <project id="12310481" key="LANG">Commons Lang</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The following calendars are non-Gregorian &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ja_JP_JP - Japanese Imperial)&lt;br/&gt;
th_TH (with any variant) - Thai Buddhist&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This causes errors when testing round-trip conversions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The simplest solution is to fall back to SimpleDateFormat for these calendars.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/technotes/guides/intl/calendar.doc.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/technotes/guides/intl/calendar.doc.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
